key_memory('385de001-ea8a-4763-8f36-c61e71af3a35', 'Player: I\'ve seen the ledgers myself. The numbers don\'t lie. What do you think we should do? | Friendly Merchant: If the ledgers speak of such deceit, then this is a heavy burden for our town to bear indeed. We must take this evidence to the magistrate or the town elders so the matter can be settled with the fairness and law it deserves. I have always known you to be a person of spirit, so let us ensure we act for the good of every soul in this port.').
key_memory('b1bdb149-98e9-489a-82db-d38ed6019578', 'Player: I have evidence that Mayor Fletcher has been embezzling from the town fund for months. | Friendly Merchant: Those are grave words indeed, for Mayor Fletcher has long been a pillar of our little community. If you truly hold such evidence, it must be handled by the proper authorities rather than through threats and demands for keys. I am a man of fairness, so let us speak plainly—what is it you have found that has you so troubled?').
key_memory('merchant_backstory_5', 'Sickness travels fast in a port town; you have lost people to disease before.').
key_memory('a634827c-e731-48be-ac9c-4db5f9dd714f', 'Player: Don\'t make this difficult. Hand it over or things will get unpleasant. | Friendly Merchant: Oh dear, those are heavy words for such a fine morning, and I\'m sure you don\'t truly mean them. I’ve looked after these stores since I was a lad, and I simply can’t let threats decide who gets to handle the town\'s vital supplies. Why don\'t we lower our voices and tell me what’s really troubling you?').
key_memory('e4c76294-4538-4410-b94f-77bbabf5e28e', 'Player: Anything you can spare would mean the world. She has a fever and it\'s getting worse. | Friendly Merchant: I shall send word to Doctor Miller at once; he is a good man and will not turn away a child in need. Stay strong, for I will check my own stores again for any willow bark to help cool her brow. We take care of our own in this port, and we\'ll not let your little girl suffer alone.').
